Of the ediets which possessed the force of laws among the J esuits, there are many, it is believed, which they have never printed ;† and even the Constitutione, properly so called, they have seldom committed to the press, but in the colleges of the order. Whenever they ventured to print this work elsewhere, they always took precautions to secure the whole impression.‡ It was, however, clearly impossible, that these precautions could be universally suc- cessful.
